1
00:00:38,496 --> 00:00:39,622
-Surprise!
-Surprise!

2
00:00:39,706 --> 00:00:41,124
-Dad! Mom!
-Mikoy!

3
00:00:41,207 --> 00:00:42,167
My son!

4
00:00:43,960 --> 00:00:47,630
How about the one I asked
you to investigate?

5
00:00:48,214 --> 00:00:49,257
Here it is, sir.

6
00:00:49,340 --> 00:00:51,176
He hasn't achieved anything in life.

7
00:00:51,259 --> 00:00:52,469
He's very simple.

8
00:00:52,552 --> 00:00:53,386
Chiara, sorry.

9
00:00:53,470 --> 00:00:57,140
I just don't want you to think
that I'm taking advantage of your family.

10
00:00:57,223 --> 00:00:59,142
That's why I accepted your dad's offer.

11
00:00:59,225 --> 00:01:00,143
Hurry!

12
00:01:00,226 --> 00:01:03,438
-Chiara's parents are here!
-What?!

13
00:01:03,521 --> 00:01:05,523
Mr. and Mrs. Valtrovi?

14
00:01:15,241 --> 00:01:16,076
Oh!

15
00:01:21,915 --> 00:01:25,001
Tell Mikoy what we decided.

16
00:01:26,544 --> 00:01:30,965
Well, we finally got the blessing
of your mom and dad.

17
00:01:36,054 --> 00:01:37,138
-Oh!
-This weekend!

18
00:01:39,182 --> 00:01:40,558
Yes, sweetheart.

19
00:01:41,434 --> 00:01:42,727
Yay!

20
00:01:44,062 --> 00:01:45,396
Yes, sweetheart!

21
00:01:45,480 --> 00:01:47,148
We're getting married!

22
00:01:47,857 --> 00:01:52,028
We'll be Mr. and Mrs. Pinagpala!

23
00:02:06,709 --> 00:02:08,336
Son! Mikoy!

24
00:02:08,419 --> 00:02:10,505
He really loves pulling pranks.

25
00:02:10,588 --> 00:02:12,298
Whether in Prague or the Philippines,

26
00:02:12,382 --> 00:02:14,175
he's always up to something!

27
00:02:14,801 --> 00:02:16,344
Oh my, come here! Let's eat!

28
00:02:16,427 --> 00:02:18,429
I really love this… What do you call it?
Sweet cake!

29
00:02:18,513 --> 00:02:19,347
-Come on!
-The sweet cake.

30
00:02:19,430 --> 00:02:20,932
Oh, this is his fault.

31
00:02:21,015 --> 00:02:21,891
He arrived late.

32
00:02:21,975 --> 00:02:22,600
-Come on.
-Come on.

33
00:02:22,684 --> 00:02:23,935
Let's eat first.

34
00:02:24,018 --> 00:02:24,894
I'm sorry, sweetheart.

35
00:02:24,978 --> 00:02:27,689
It was Papa's idea.

36
00:02:29,524 --> 00:02:31,985
It was also your Dad Mario's idea!

37
00:02:32,068 --> 00:02:33,820
If I love joking around,

38
00:02:33,903 --> 00:02:36,072
your dad is even worse!

39
00:02:36,156 --> 00:02:37,407
Hey, in-law!

40
00:02:37,490 --> 00:02:40,743
No flopping around.
I thought we were besties!

41
00:02:40,827 --> 00:02:43,121
Look at you calling him "in-law"!

42
00:02:44,539 --> 00:02:45,790
But what is "balae"?

43
00:02:45,874 --> 00:02:47,083
"Balae",

44
00:02:47,167 --> 00:02:48,918
in English, means we are family.

45
00:02:50,962 --> 00:02:54,549
So then, allow me to be your "in-law",

46
00:02:54,632 --> 00:02:56,801
Daddy Mario and Mommy Tess!

47
00:03:00,805 --> 00:03:02,098
Mikoy,

48
00:03:02,181 --> 00:03:05,101
have you told them why
you came back to the Philippines?

49
00:03:05,184 --> 00:03:06,769
Wait.

50
00:03:07,312 --> 00:03:09,397
Aren't you here just for a vacation?

51
00:03:09,480 --> 00:03:11,065
You and Chiara.

52
00:03:11,149 --> 00:03:13,818
Just relaxing from work.
Something like that, right?

53
00:03:14,402 --> 00:03:16,988
I've just been looking
for the right moment to tell you.

54
00:03:17,071 --> 00:03:18,615
Dad, Mom.

55
00:03:23,244 --> 00:03:24,537
I'm sick, Mom.

56
00:03:26,623 --> 00:03:28,207
I've been given a limited time to live.

57
00:03:31,294 --> 00:03:33,254
I only have a few days left, Mom.

58
00:03:34,505 --> 00:03:36,341
What illness are you talking about?

59
00:03:36,925 --> 00:03:39,135
Mikoy, what? What happened?

60
00:03:39,219 --> 00:03:40,845
What illness are you talking about?

61
00:03:40,929 --> 00:03:41,763
Mikoy!

62
00:03:42,555 --> 00:03:43,473
Because…

63
00:03:44,224 --> 00:03:45,600
They said, Mom…

64
00:03:47,185 --> 00:03:48,019
Just kidding!

65
00:03:49,229 --> 00:03:50,688
Mikoy!

66
00:03:51,564 --> 00:03:53,233
Oh my, this kid!

67
00:03:58,363 --> 00:04:00,406
Our asset, Mikoy, confirmed

68
00:04:00,490 --> 00:04:02,617
that the Valtrovi's are here,
in the Philippines.

69
00:04:02,700 --> 00:04:05,078
Why would they come to the Philippines?

70
00:04:09,082 --> 00:04:12,043
Away from their influence
in the European Union?

71
00:04:12,126 --> 00:04:13,419
What they're doing is dangerous.

72
00:04:13,503 --> 00:04:15,255
They're not protected here.

73
00:04:17,006 --> 00:04:18,383
That's what I find strange, too.

74
00:04:45,702 --> 00:04:47,620
The truth is,

75
00:04:47,704 --> 00:04:50,123
Mikoy has grown close to us.

76
00:04:53,876 --> 00:04:59,215
And in such a short time,
we realized how hardworking he is.

77
00:04:59,799 --> 00:05:01,509
Very hardworking.

78
00:05:01,592 --> 00:05:03,344
And very kind, too.

79
00:05:18,651 --> 00:05:21,237
Like you said, in-law,

80
00:05:21,738 --> 00:05:22,989
we are now one family.

81
00:05:24,032 --> 00:05:26,659
So, who else should I trust but family?

82
00:05:27,493 --> 00:05:29,162
I know he can run my business.

83
00:05:30,705 --> 00:05:35,877
And he won't have to be far away
from his own family.

84
00:05:35,960 --> 00:05:37,295
-That's Tagalog, huh.
-Well, in-law.

85
00:05:37,378 --> 00:05:38,421
If that's the case,

86
00:05:39,297 --> 00:05:40,673
we should have another party!

87
00:05:40,757 --> 00:05:41,883
-Right!
-Wow!

88
00:05:41,966 --> 00:05:43,384
-I love it! I like that!
-Okay.

89
00:05:43,468 --> 00:05:44,469
-Oh yeah!
-Party! Party!

90
00:05:44,552 --> 00:05:46,888
-In-law!
-Yes!

91
00:05:46,971 --> 00:05:48,264
Betchay!

92
00:06:42,527 --> 00:06:44,237
Hold on. Stop hitting…

93
00:06:48,658 --> 00:06:51,410
My parents are clearly
enjoying their stay.

94
00:06:51,494 --> 00:06:52,995
Yeah, right!

95
00:06:53,496 --> 00:06:55,790
Uncle Vik is really showing off his moves,

96
00:06:55,873 --> 00:06:57,625
like John Travolta!

97
00:06:59,669 --> 00:07:01,796
-Where's your Mom and Dad?
-Huh?

98
00:07:02,839 --> 00:07:03,923
They're probably upstairs,

99
00:07:04,006 --> 00:07:06,342
getting some food ready
for your mom and dad.

100
00:07:07,093 --> 00:07:09,720
-Well, there's a sudden party!
-Can we just do videoke?

101
00:07:09,804 --> 00:07:13,391
It's embarrassing
that they had to do that.

102
00:07:13,474 --> 00:07:14,976
No, it's fine.

103
00:07:15,059 --> 00:07:16,686
They are enjoying it.

104
00:07:19,230 --> 00:07:21,065
I'll help them.

105
00:07:21,649 --> 00:07:22,692
Huh?

106
00:07:22,775 --> 00:07:24,026
You sure? Okay.

107
00:07:24,110 --> 00:07:25,069
-It's fine.
-I'll come with you.

108
00:07:27,071 --> 00:07:29,449
-Mikoy! Mikoy! Join us!
-Huh?

109
00:07:29,532 --> 00:07:30,450
But…

110
00:07:30,533 --> 00:07:31,784
Okay, you take care of it.

111
00:07:31,868 --> 00:07:33,244
-You can handle it!
-Come on. Dance with us.

112
00:07:33,327 --> 00:07:34,203
-Huh?
-Dance with us!

113
00:07:34,287 --> 00:07:36,080
-You can do it!
-Dance with us.

114
00:07:37,039 --> 00:07:37,874
Okay.

115
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:40,543
Move like this.

116
00:07:50,678 --> 00:07:51,637
You know, darling,

117
00:07:51,721 --> 00:07:54,474
I'm thankful to Viktor.

118
00:07:54,557 --> 00:07:57,560
But does Mikoy really need

119
00:07:58,394 --> 00:08:02,690
to work at his girlfriend's dad's company?

120
00:08:02,773 --> 00:08:03,733
What is the problem?

121
00:08:03,816 --> 00:08:06,986
First, he'll probably get a good salary.

122
00:08:07,069 --> 00:08:09,906
Second, Mikoy no longer needs
to go back to Prague.

123
00:08:09,989 --> 00:08:11,908
He will stay close to us.

124
00:08:11,991 --> 00:08:13,868
You know, you're right.

125
00:08:13,951 --> 00:08:16,579
But this is just what I'm thinking.

126
00:08:17,288 --> 00:08:18,623
The truth is,

127
00:08:18,706 --> 00:08:22,627
they can't accept Mikoy for who he is.

128
00:08:22,710 --> 00:08:24,754
That's why they want to change him.

129
00:08:25,338 --> 00:08:26,172
You know,

130
00:08:26,255 --> 00:08:29,300
I would think the same
if I were in their position.

131
00:08:29,383 --> 00:08:31,385
I also wouldn't want

132
00:08:31,469 --> 00:08:34,805
my daughter's boyfriend
to be just a waiter.

133
00:08:34,889 --> 00:08:38,434
Of course, what I'd do
is give him a better job,

134
00:08:38,518 --> 00:08:40,394
something more acceptable,

135
00:08:40,478 --> 00:08:41,437
right?

136
00:08:42,897 --> 00:08:43,981
So, what's wrong with that?

137
00:08:44,565 --> 00:08:46,150
Tess, don't think that way.

138
00:08:46,234 --> 00:08:49,779
I want to believe
that Viktor and Donabel are sincere

139
00:08:49,862 --> 00:08:52,573
in wanting to help Mikoy.

140
00:08:52,657 --> 00:08:55,409
They want to give him a better job.

141
00:09:03,167 --> 00:09:04,710
I don't know.

142
00:09:05,711 --> 00:09:08,381
I can't explain the reason for this,

143
00:09:08,464 --> 00:09:11,175
but I'm really scared for our son.

144
00:09:11,259 --> 00:09:12,927
Scared of what?

145
00:09:13,010 --> 00:09:14,470
I don't even know.

146
00:09:14,554 --> 00:09:18,808
But I'm really anxious
that something might happen to our child

147
00:09:19,392 --> 00:09:21,811
if he accepts that job.

148
00:09:37,243 --> 00:09:40,162
Boss, here's our delivery for this month.

149
00:09:41,747 --> 00:09:42,665
It's all complete.

150
00:09:44,625 --> 00:09:47,628
Just always be on the lookout.

151
00:09:47,712 --> 00:09:48,838
Okay, Boss.

152
00:09:48,921 --> 00:09:51,924
But do we really need to bring that
Michael Pinagpala into the company?

153
00:09:52,008 --> 00:09:54,010
He might ruin all our plans.

154
00:09:54,093 --> 00:09:55,261
We don't have a choice.

155
00:09:55,344 --> 00:09:58,514
This is his daughter's fault
for falling for that nobody.

156
00:09:58,598 --> 00:10:01,517
So you'll just allow it, Boss?
That he would take over your position?

157
00:10:03,102 --> 00:10:06,355
I won't let that bastard
take everything I worked hard for.

158
00:10:06,439 --> 00:10:07,857
So what's our plan now?

159
00:10:07,940 --> 00:10:10,860
We will have to find a way
to eliminate him

160
00:10:10,943 --> 00:10:12,987
before he ruins our plans.

161
00:10:17,199 --> 00:10:19,410
I will kill him

162
00:10:19,493 --> 00:10:20,911
before he interferes.

163
00:10:23,289 --> 00:10:24,915
-What was that?
-Someone's there!

164
00:10:24,999 --> 00:10:26,083
Go after him!

165
00:12:19,738 --> 00:12:22,158
-There she is.
-She's pretty, right?

166
00:12:23,200 --> 00:12:25,244
-Nice!
-There she is! Chiara!

167
00:12:25,327 --> 00:12:26,620
Chiara, come on. Join us.

168
00:12:26,704 --> 00:12:28,372
Your mom and dad have great moves.

169
00:12:28,456 --> 00:12:29,748
They're really killing it.

170
00:12:34,086 --> 00:12:36,714
Come on! Join us! Look! It's so fun!

171
00:12:43,220 --> 00:12:45,556
My dear. Are you okay?

172
00:12:47,266 --> 00:12:48,476
Yes, Papa.

173
00:12:48,559 --> 00:12:50,728
It feels like something has changed.

174
00:12:51,854 --> 00:12:54,648
What happened? What is that?

175
00:12:55,149 --> 00:12:57,026
I just remembered something.

176
00:12:57,860 --> 00:13:01,155
My dear, do not overthink.

177
00:13:07,244 --> 00:13:08,829
You're right! I agree.

178
00:13:13,959 --> 00:13:15,711
No! Of course not, dear.

179
00:13:15,794 --> 00:13:17,421
There's no problem at all.

180
00:13:17,505 --> 00:13:19,673
If you like, you can stay here tonight.

181
00:13:19,757 --> 00:13:21,342
Yes. Don't think about that,

182
00:13:21,425 --> 00:13:23,093
because we're glad that you're here.

183
00:13:23,177 --> 00:13:25,596
And it's even better
because we got to meet you.

184
00:13:27,640 --> 00:13:30,559
Thank you, Uncle and Auntie,

185
00:13:30,643 --> 00:13:34,063
but we've already caused
too much trouble for you.

186
00:13:38,734 --> 00:13:40,528
We'll just stay at a hotel.

187
00:13:42,696 --> 00:13:43,948
Okay, sure.

188
00:13:44,573 --> 00:13:46,909
-I'll accompany you--
-No, it's fine!

189
00:13:47,409 --> 00:13:48,494
We'll handle it ourselves.

190
00:13:51,914 --> 00:13:53,707
Alright. Okay.

191
00:13:53,791 --> 00:13:55,292
-Mikoy…
-Take care.

192
00:13:55,376 --> 00:13:58,587
Thank you so much for having us here.

193
00:14:00,673 --> 00:14:02,591
See you soon, in-law.

194
00:14:02,675 --> 00:14:04,385
In-law, thank you so much!

195
00:14:04,468 --> 00:14:05,761
Oh, sorry about that.

196
00:14:06,345 --> 00:14:07,721
But we'll definitely come back.

197
00:14:08,472 --> 00:14:10,099
Because my husband enjoyed it,

198
00:14:10,182 --> 00:14:11,350
not just me.

199
00:14:11,433 --> 00:14:12,518
Right.

200
00:14:12,601 --> 00:14:14,853
-Ouch.
-You're welcome, in-law.

201
00:14:16,313 --> 00:14:17,481
-Take care.
-We'll come back.

202
00:14:40,087 --> 00:14:41,255
You go ahead.

203
00:14:41,338 --> 00:14:42,923
Go ahead!

204
00:14:49,138 --> 00:14:50,389
Dear.

205
00:14:51,348 --> 00:14:53,392
You think Chiara's okay?

206
00:14:55,853 --> 00:14:57,271
Her mood suddenly changed, right?

207
00:14:58,772 --> 00:15:00,733
It's like you said.

208
00:15:01,233 --> 00:15:03,569
It's worse than having a monthly period.

209
00:15:04,278 --> 00:15:05,571
I was shocked with her reaction.

210
00:15:05,654 --> 00:15:06,947
You're right.

211
00:15:07,865 --> 00:15:09,909
I was shocked, too.

212
00:15:11,035 --> 00:15:12,578
Is she really like that?

213
00:15:12,661 --> 00:15:14,538
Her mood suddenly changes?

214
00:15:15,122 --> 00:15:16,040
Yes.

215
00:15:16,582 --> 00:15:17,458
What do you call that?

216
00:15:19,126 --> 00:15:20,794
She has mood swings?

217
00:15:21,795 --> 00:15:23,380
Not really, Dad.

218
00:15:23,464 --> 00:15:24,590
Usually,

219
00:15:25,090 --> 00:15:27,051
she's just having fun.

220
00:15:27,134 --> 00:15:29,386
You know, just always chilling.

221
00:15:29,887 --> 00:15:32,222
She has no major hang-ups in life.

222
00:15:32,306 --> 00:15:37,770
Maybe she heard something bad
about her and her family.

223
00:15:38,354 --> 00:15:41,607
I can't recall anything I said
that could offend her.

224
00:15:42,650 --> 00:15:44,026
Actually,

225
00:15:44,109 --> 00:15:46,612
we were enjoying
talking to each other earlier.

226
00:15:47,112 --> 00:15:48,322
Then suddenly that happened.

227
00:15:48,405 --> 00:15:51,075
Maybe it's not you, Mikoy.

228
00:15:51,659 --> 00:15:54,578
Maybe she heard it from other people.

229
00:15:55,329 --> 00:15:56,372
Who?

230
00:15:56,872 --> 00:15:57,998
From Mom and Dad?

231
00:15:58,082 --> 00:16:00,084
Oh! I don't know.

232
00:16:00,167 --> 00:16:01,835
But who else?

233
00:16:01,919 --> 00:16:03,754
Is there anyone else here in the house?

234
00:16:03,837 --> 00:16:06,840
Stop with your mumbling!

235
00:16:06,924 --> 00:16:08,926
Tell us. Be straightforward.

236
00:16:09,009 --> 00:16:12,471
Do you know why there's a sudden change

237
00:16:12,554 --> 00:16:14,640
-and why Chiara's mood changed?
-Right.

238
00:16:14,723 --> 00:16:17,059
Alright. I'll be the one to speak,

239
00:16:17,142 --> 00:16:19,311
because I'm the only one
who knows the truth

240
00:16:21,522 --> 00:16:23,857
Wow! No more beating around the bush!

241
00:16:23,941 --> 00:16:25,025
Just say it!

242
00:16:25,109 --> 00:16:26,735
You're impatient!

243
00:16:26,819 --> 00:16:27,987
This is what happened.

244
00:16:28,070 --> 00:16:31,365
Earlier, I saw her.

245
00:16:31,448 --> 00:16:36,787
I don't know why,
but I am really worried about our child.

246
00:16:36,870 --> 00:16:38,372
What are you worried about?

247
00:16:38,455 --> 00:16:42,459
Because I know something bad
might happen if he accepts that job.

248
00:16:44,878 --> 00:16:45,963
Mom?

249
00:16:46,046 --> 00:16:46,922
Dad?

250
00:16:47,965 --> 00:16:49,633
Why did you say that?

251
00:16:50,884 --> 00:16:52,678
I already told your mom earlier.

252
00:16:53,971 --> 00:16:55,681
She shouldn't speak like that.

253
00:16:56,724 --> 00:16:59,143
She shouldn't say something bad
about Chiara's family.

254
00:16:59,727 --> 00:17:00,728
Wow!

255
00:17:00,811 --> 00:17:01,979
You're letting me take the fall.

256
00:17:02,062 --> 00:17:03,522
It's true, right?

257
00:17:06,275 --> 00:17:07,568
Mikoy.

258
00:17:07,651 --> 00:17:10,821
I didn't mean for Chiara to hear that.

259
00:17:12,948 --> 00:17:15,909
But you can't stop me from worrying.

260
00:17:15,993 --> 00:17:17,494
Of course,

261
00:17:17,578 --> 00:17:20,080
I was also shocked by what happened.

262
00:17:20,164 --> 00:17:22,082
Think about it.

263
00:17:22,166 --> 00:17:25,085
You went to Prague for work.

264
00:17:25,169 --> 00:17:28,756
Then you suddenly came back with Chiara.

265
00:17:29,381 --> 00:17:30,799
Then, surprisingly,

266
00:17:31,383 --> 00:17:33,844
her mom and dad came, too.

267
00:17:34,887 --> 00:17:37,598
Of course, it got me thinking.

268
00:17:37,681 --> 00:17:39,600
What's happening?

269
00:17:40,601 --> 00:17:42,644
Feels like something's wrong.

270
00:17:42,728 --> 00:17:45,189
Maybe you're just surprised
by your own decisions.

271
00:17:46,565 --> 00:17:47,858
Mom, Dad.

272
00:17:48,525 --> 00:17:52,362
I know it feels like everything is sudden.

273
00:17:53,405 --> 00:17:55,157
But believe me,

274
00:17:56,700 --> 00:17:58,660
this is for everyone's good.

275
00:17:59,912 --> 00:18:01,080
Promise.

276
00:18:02,581 --> 00:18:04,583
I know that, son.

277
00:18:05,584 --> 00:18:10,631
But it's my duty to overthink
and worry about my child, right?

278
00:18:10,714 --> 00:18:11,673
Of course.

279
00:18:11,757 --> 00:18:14,134
But I promise you, dear.

280
00:18:14,218 --> 00:18:17,137
I'll visit Chiara tomorrow

281
00:18:17,221 --> 00:18:19,098
and explain everything to her.

282
00:18:19,181 --> 00:18:25,354
And I'll apologize to her
if I hurt her feelings

283
00:18:25,437 --> 00:18:27,231
because of what I said earlier.

284
00:18:30,484 --> 00:18:32,152
Please forgive your mom.

285
00:18:33,612 --> 00:18:35,030
Because everything she does

286
00:18:35,906 --> 00:18:39,118
and thinks is what's best for you.

287
00:18:42,788 --> 00:18:44,039
Even if she acts that way,

288
00:18:44,873 --> 00:18:46,125
she's still your mom.

289
00:18:46,792 --> 00:18:48,877
-I don't know about you!
-Sir…

290
00:18:49,378 --> 00:18:52,047
-Come here. You!
-Ouch. That hurts.

291
00:18:52,131 --> 00:18:54,299
-That was hard.
-And you…

292
00:18:54,383 --> 00:18:56,009
You're always throwing me under the bus.

293
00:18:56,093 --> 00:18:57,177
You were talking too much.

294
00:18:57,261 --> 00:18:59,304
But earlier, you sold me out!

295
00:19:02,099 --> 00:19:03,183
That hurts.

296
00:19:12,442 --> 00:19:14,486
Is there anything wrong, dear?

297
00:19:16,155 --> 00:19:17,489
Did we say anything wrong?

298
00:19:17,573 --> 00:19:19,908
Did we do something wrong?

299
00:19:46,768 --> 00:19:48,979
Mikoy! Mikoy!

300
00:19:49,062 --> 00:19:50,606
Pinagpala!

301
00:19:50,689 --> 00:19:52,232
Darling!

302
00:19:52,316 --> 00:19:53,150
PINAGPALA
SPECIAL BAKESHOP

303
00:19:55,152 --> 00:19:56,862
Oh, wait. Did you have breakfast?

304
00:19:56,945 --> 00:19:58,280
-Badong!
-Don't bother, ma'am.

305
00:19:58,363 --> 00:19:59,656
I'm fine, ma'am.

306
00:19:59,740 --> 00:20:00,782
Thank you!

307
00:20:02,326 --> 00:20:04,077
Where's Uncle Vik?

308
00:20:04,161 --> 00:20:06,622
Oh, that fool.

309
00:20:06,705 --> 00:20:07,748
He went back to Manila.

310
00:20:07,831 --> 00:20:11,793
He has business, as usual, to attend to.

311
00:20:12,377 --> 00:20:13,712
But wait a minute.

312
00:20:14,296 --> 00:20:16,757
Are you looking for Viktor or Chiara?

313
00:20:18,634 --> 00:20:20,010
I'm looking for…

314
00:20:20,719 --> 00:20:21,678
Chiara, ma'am.

315
00:20:23,180 --> 00:20:25,015
I shouldn't ask, right? Isn't it obvious?

316
00:20:27,351 --> 00:20:28,310
Kind of.

317
00:20:29,061 --> 00:20:31,480
You know, my daughter seems worried.

318
00:20:31,980 --> 00:20:35,692
I noticed she seems to be deep in thought.

319
00:20:36,401 --> 00:20:38,195
She even mentioned
she wants to go back to Prague.

320
00:20:38,278 --> 00:20:40,280
What is this? Wait, did you have a fight?

321
00:20:41,198 --> 00:20:42,699
No, ma'am.

322
00:20:42,783 --> 00:20:45,911
Actually, I wanted to talk to her.

323
00:20:46,411 --> 00:20:48,372
She probably heard something bad.

324
00:20:48,455 --> 00:20:51,291
That's why she's acting that way.

325
00:20:51,375 --> 00:20:53,752
You know what? You can make it up to her.

326
00:20:53,835 --> 00:20:56,505
Well, you can use your charm now!

327
00:20:56,588 --> 00:20:59,967
Convince her, so we can stay here.

328
00:21:00,050 --> 00:21:01,802
I haven't been to the beach yet!

329
00:21:03,929 --> 00:21:05,305
Oh, wait a minute!

330
00:21:05,389 --> 00:21:06,723
Is that it?

331
00:21:06,807 --> 00:21:09,059
-You didn't bring anything?
-What?

332
00:21:10,185 --> 00:21:14,273
Oh my! Well, my daughter,
aside from the fact that we look alike,

333
00:21:14,356 --> 00:21:15,857
our habits are also similar.

334
00:21:15,941 --> 00:21:19,569
What you need to do when you woo her,
is to bring something like…

335
00:21:19,653 --> 00:21:20,696
Flowers!

336
00:21:22,072 --> 00:21:23,323
You didn't bring any?

337
00:21:25,617 --> 00:21:26,785
-Nothing.
-Wait, here!

338
00:21:34,209 --> 00:21:35,627
Badong, please clean this up.

339
00:21:35,711 --> 00:21:37,337
Here, let's get three.

340
00:21:38,588 --> 00:21:41,133
There you go. It means "I…

341
00:21:41,216 --> 00:21:42,509
am sorry."

342
00:21:44,052 --> 00:21:45,220
Go straight to her!

343
00:21:45,304 --> 00:21:46,722
That's her room.

344
00:21:46,805 --> 00:21:48,015
-Oh, okay.
-Come on, lover boy.

345
00:21:48,098 --> 00:21:50,392
-There!
-Thank you!

346
00:21:51,560 --> 00:21:52,853
-Wait a minute!
-Thank you!

347
00:21:52,936 --> 00:21:54,730
Don't try to woo me.

348
00:21:54,813 --> 00:21:56,106
That was a close kiss on the lips.

349
00:21:56,189 --> 00:21:57,899
Be thankful…

350
00:21:57,983 --> 00:21:59,401
Okay, hurry!

351
00:22:18,337 --> 00:22:20,339
I'll call you. Just be ready!

352
00:22:32,267 --> 00:22:33,351
Mikoy?

353
00:22:35,312 --> 00:22:36,313
Mikoy?

354
00:22:41,151 --> 00:22:42,778
What are you doing?

355
00:22:42,861 --> 00:22:43,862
Why would you do that?

356
00:22:43,945 --> 00:22:45,822
I don't like being startled.

357
00:22:45,906 --> 00:22:48,241
This was actually your mom's idea.

358
00:22:48,325 --> 00:22:49,910
That I should make it up to you.

359
00:22:50,619 --> 00:22:53,955
I didn't know that
you're a jōnin of Konoha!

360
00:22:57,084 --> 00:22:59,211
I took karate lessons
since I was four years old,

361
00:22:59,294 --> 00:23:01,088
so I know how to defend myself.

362
00:23:09,971 --> 00:23:11,223
Isn't it obvious?

363
00:23:13,517 --> 00:23:16,311
I can see that you're in a bad mood.

364
00:23:18,230 --> 00:23:20,107
Even if you don't say anything,

365
00:23:20,607 --> 00:23:22,317
it's written all over your face

366
00:23:22,400 --> 00:23:24,778
that something
was bothering you last night.

367
00:23:28,365 --> 00:23:29,282
Chiara.

368
00:23:35,455 --> 00:23:36,957
Can we talk?

369
00:23:37,749 --> 00:23:39,042
Please?

370
00:23:40,961 --> 00:23:42,587
Heart to heart.

371
00:23:44,381 --> 00:23:46,466
So I can know what the problem is.

372
00:24:22,460 --> 00:24:25,630
Are you sure about
the complications you're getting into?

373
00:24:26,214 --> 00:24:28,049
Do you know what gives me courage?

374
00:24:28,133 --> 00:24:30,010
-What?
-You.

375
00:24:39,519 --> 00:24:43,732
I believe you now have eyes and ears
inside their organization.

376
00:24:52,824 --> 00:24:54,826
You just have to believe in yourself.
